    public final class ImmutableHashedArraySet<E>
extends java.util.AbstractSet<E>
implements ArrayBackedSet<E>, java.io.Serializable
    A Set backed by an array of elements, and a separate int array of hash codes. The arrays are the exact length required to contain the elements, and their corresponding hash codes.

    Elements are tested using a linear search implementation. Searches are performed by testing the hash codes. If the hash codes match, the element is then tested for equality. This allows for a fast, cache-friendly, linear scan of elements in the set.

    The set may also be view as a List, which implements the RandomAccess interface to indicate constant time random access.
